<h2>ChatGPT Statistics (2026)</h2>
<p>ChatGPT remains the dominant AI search platform. But its lead is narrowing at an accelerating pace.</p>
<p><strong>1. ChatGPT holds 64.5% of AI chatbot traffic share.</strong>
That figure is down from 86.7% one year prior, according to <a href="https://thedigitalbloom.com/learn/gen-ai-website-traffic-share-february-2026/">The Digital Bloom</a>. That is a 22-point drop in 12 months.</p>
<p><strong>2. ChatGPT drives 87.4% of all AI referral traffic to websites.</strong>
Despite its shrinking chatbot share, ChatGPT still dominates when it comes to actual clicks out to websites. Data from <a href="https://conductor.com/academy/aeo-geo-benchmarks-report/">Conductor's AEO/GEO Benchmarks Report</a> shows no other platform comes close on referral volume.</p>
<p><strong>3. ChatGPT has 883M monthly users and 5.4B global monthly visits.</strong>
<a href="https://exposureninja.com/blog/ai-search-statistics/">Exposure Ninja</a> places its reach at a scale larger than most traditional media properties.</p>
<p><strong>4. Weekly active users reached 900M.</strong>
<a href="https://firstpagesage.com/seo-blog/chatgpt-usage-statistics/">First Page Sage</a> reported this figure for early 2026, placing ChatGPT among the most-used applications in internet history.</p>
<p><strong>5. ChatGPT's app market share fell from 69.1% to 45.3%.</strong>
<a href="https://fortune.com/2026/02/05/chatgpt-openai-market-share-app-slip-google-rivals-close-the-gap/">Fortune</a> reported this mobile app share decline. Competitors are closing the gap on every front.</p>
<p>The referral traffic advantage ChatGPT holds is critical for SEO strategy. Even as its share of chatbot conversations falls, it still sends the most visitors to external sites. Learn how to <a href="/blog/track-ai-search-visibility/">track AI search visibility</a> before you optimize for it.</p>
<h2>Google Gemini Statistics (2026)</h2>
<p>Gemini is the fastest-growing platform in AI search. Its growth is not incremental. It is structural, driven by Google's integration of Gemini across Search, Android, and Workspace.</p>
<p><strong>6. Gemini holds 21.5% AI chatbot market share, up from 5.7% one year ago.</strong>
That represents <a href="https://sedestral.com/en/blog/ai-search-market-share-2026">647% year-over-year growth</a>. No other platform in the AI search category has grown at this rate.</p>
<p><strong>7. Gemini receives 2B monthly visits and has 650M monthly active users.</strong>
<a href="https://sedestral.com/en/blog/ai-search-market-share-2026">Sedestral's 2026 AI market share report</a> places Gemini as a clear second to ChatGPT in raw traffic volume.</p>
<p><strong>8. Gemini's mobile app share grew from 14.7% to 25.2%.</strong>
<a href="https://vertu.com/lifestyle/ai-chatbot-market-share-2026-chatgpt-drops-to-68-as-google-gemini-surges-to-18-2/">Vertu's analysis</a> tracked this shift over 12 months. As ChatGPT's app share fell, Gemini absorbed much of the difference.</p>
<p>Gemini's growth has direct implications for how Google ranks AI Overview content. Read our post on <a href="/blog/optimize-google-ai-overviews/">how to optimize for Google AI Overviews</a> to understand what this shift demands from your content.</p>
<h2>Perplexity AI Statistics (2026)</h2>
<p>Perplexity is the most search-native AI platform. It is built specifically to answer queries with cited sources, which makes it both a competitor to Google and a potential referral driver for content-rich sites.</p>
<p><strong>9. Perplexity holds between 6.4% and 8% of the AI chatbot market.</strong>
<a href="https://seoprofy.com/blog/perplexity-ai-statistics/">Seoprofy's Perplexity statistics report</a> places it as the clear third-largest platform by market share.</p>
<p><strong>10. Perplexity has 45M monthly active users and 170M monthly visitors.</strong>
For context: Perplexity generates roughly 8x its MAU count in monthly visits, suggesting a high frequency of use per active user. Source: <a href="https://seoprofy.com/blog/perplexity-ai-statistics/">Seoprofy</a>.</p>
<p><strong>11. Perplexity includes links in 77% or more of its responses.</strong>
This is the highest link citation rate of any major AI search platform. <a href="https://get-spotlight.com/articles/how-to-measure-and-improve-brand-share-of-voice-in-ai-chatbots-and-llms-a-step-by-step-guide/">Spotlight's research</a> shows Perplexity is architecturally built to surface and cite sources.</p>
<p>That 77% link rate makes Perplexity disproportionately valuable for content that earns placement. If you want your content to appear there, read our guide on <a href="/blog/optimize-for-perplexity-ai/">how to optimize for Perplexity AI</a>.</p>
<h2>Claude, Copilot, and Other Platforms</h2>
<p><strong>12. Claude holds approximately 2% to 3.2% of AI chatbot market share.</strong>
With 30M monthly active users, Claude trails the top 2 platforms significantly in volume. Source: <a href="https://seoprofy.com/blog/perplexity-ai-statistics/">Seoprofy</a>.</p>
<p><strong>13. Claude mentions brands in 97.3% of its responses.</strong>
This is the highest brand mention rate of any major AI platform, according to <a href="https://get-spotlight.com/articles/how-to-measure-and-improve-brand-share-of-voice-in-ai-chatbots-and-llms-a-step-by-step-guide/">Spotlight's LLM brand visibility research</a>. For brands optimizing for generative engine visibility, Claude's behavior matters even at lower traffic volumes.</p>
<p><strong>14. Microsoft Copilot has 33M active users.</strong>
<a href="https://seoprofy.com/blog/perplexity-ai-statistics/">Seoprofy</a> places Copilot in a similar range to Claude by user count. Copilot benefits from enterprise Microsoft 365 distribution, not consumer demand.</p>
