<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<p><strong>What is the current AI search market share breakdown?</strong></p>
<p>As of early 2026, ChatGPT holds approximately 64.5% of AI chatbot traffic share, Gemini holds 21.5%, Perplexity holds 6–8%, and Claude holds 2–3%. Copilot accounts for roughly 2%. ChatGPT's share has fallen sharply from 86.7% one year prior. Source: <a href="https://thedigitalbloom.com/learn/gen-ai-website-traffic-share-february-2026/">The Digital Bloom</a>, <a href="https://sedestral.com/en/blog/ai-search-market-share-2026">Sedestral</a>.</p>
<p><strong>How much traffic do AI search platforms send to websites?</strong></p>
<p>AI referral traffic accounts for 1.08% of total web traffic as measured by <a href="https://conductor.com/academy/aeo-geo-benchmarks-report/">Conductor</a>. ChatGPT is responsible for 87.4% of all AI-originated referral clicks. The percentage is small but the conversion quality is high. AI visitors convert at 2x the average rate. See our glossary entry on <a href="/glossary/ai-overviews/">AI Overviews</a> for related definitions.</p>
<p><strong>Why does GA4 undercount AI search traffic?</strong></p>
<p><a href="https://thedigitalbloom.com/learn/gen-ai-website-traffic-share-february-2026/">The Digital Bloom found</a> that 70.6% of AI referral sessions are misclassified as direct traffic in GA4. This happens because many AI platforms do not pass referrer headers in the standard way that analytics tools expect. Without proper UTM tracking or server-side logging, most businesses do not see their true AI search traffic numbers.</p>
<p><strong>How fast is Gemini growing compared to ChatGPT?</strong></p>
<p>Gemini grew 647% year over year. From 5.7% to 21.5% market share. While ChatGPT fell by 22 percentage points. At the current trajectory, Gemini is the only platform positioned to challenge ChatGPT's lead within the next 1–2 years. Source: <a href="https://sedestral.com/en/blog/ai-search-market-share-2026">Sedestral</a>. For context on what this means for your visibility, read our comparison of <a href="/blog/gemini-vs-chatgpt-search/">Gemini vs ChatGPT for search</a>.</p>
<p>AI search market share is still in flux. The platforms gaining ground fastest. Gemini and Perplexity. Are the ones most focused on sourcing and citing content. Businesses that publish consistently, target specific queries, and track attribution correctly are positioned to benefit from that shift.</p>
